My personal dotfiles. The .gitignore is set up to ignore everything first and then deliberately include certain files and directories into the domain of git management.

This is updated to use bashdot so it's a little easier to use with git etc. 

Clone into ~/src/dotfiles, then 

```
brew tap bashdot/tap
brew install bashdot
bashdot install src/dotfiles
```

Clone this repo into ~/dotfiles (or pick a different name), then `bashdot install dotfiles` to symlink them into your env./
